title: For Sale/Trade:  WTT/WTS CZ-82 plus lots of extras.
postcontent:
I am looking to sell my CZ-82, it's been a great gun for me, but I'd like to get something along the lines of a full sized handgun.

This is an excellent shooter, DA/SA, 12+1 capacity, fires the 9x18 Makarov round.

I am wanting to trade the gun with a bunch of extras.


Whole package includes

-(3) 12 rounds magazines with milled floorplates

-Black leather military surplus holster

-Desantis 106-v5 IWB leather gun holster, for ruger lc9 (also fits CZ-82 as shown nicely, the lip is a bit chewed up, dog got to it, but isn't uncomfortable or noticable when wearing and wears nicely.)

-(2) 50 round boxes of Brown bear 94 grain FMJ's

-(1) 50 round box of Prvi Partisan brass cased, reloadable 93 gr FMJ's

- 28 rounds of steel cased russian 9m mak ammo, 92 gr FMJ

-250 rounds of hardcast, brass cased, RN ammo, I was told these are 115 gr and are loaded to the same specs as Buffalo Bore +P rounds, which is 115 gr at 1000 fps, I have fired them and they have noticably more kick to them than regular FMJ's, so I'd attest that they are more powerful.

-6 Glaser safety slugs

-13 rounds of Hornday XTP hollopoints

The CZ-82 has an upgraded 16lb wolff recoil spring, over the factory 14 pound, helps reduce the already tame recoil.

Comes with upgraded recoil spring, the original recoil spring, and a new firing pin spring as well.

I have fired maybe 300 rounds since I got this gun, and the polygynal rifling, coupled with the fixed barrel makes this gun very accurate, I was easily able to put 12 rounds into a 3 1/2 inch group at 15 yards the first time I shot it.

Some wear on the slide, the finish has chipped off, this is very common with these guns as the finish wasn't very good, but gun functions flawlessly, have never had a FTF or FTE.


CZ-82 price = 200 + 38$ shipping + 10$ hand pick fee + 25$ FFL transfer = 278$
2 extra mags @ 22$ each + 9 $ shipping = 53$
x2 boxes of FMJ brown bear = 26$

glaser slugs, 3$
250 hardcast = 100$

Total cost for everything comes out to 508$

I'm really leaning towards a new handgun in .45 ACP, so if you have one and would like to trade it, you'll get first priority.
